Author Biography
Brian T. Wymbs, PhD, is an assistant professor of psychology 
at Ohio University. His primary research interests focus on 
examining links between ADHD and romantic relationship dif-
ficulties. Dr. Wymbs has examined rates of interparental discord 
and divorce in families including children with ADHD, as well 
as rates of intimate partner violence and potential explanatory 
factors among young adults with ADHD.

## Results
Results: 
Adults with ADHD whose self-control resources were depleted communicated less positively and more negatively with 
their romantic partners than adults without ADHD whose resources were depleted.

## Clinical Significance
Conclusion: Adults with ADHD 
appear to have a differential susceptibility to interpartner discord when their self-control resources have been depleted. 
Clinicians seeking to remediate discordant romantic relationships of adults with ADHD should consider evaluating how 
often their resources needed to manage their impulses are depleted. (J. of Att. Dis. XXXX; XX[X] XX-XX)
